            "item_id": 2896059873,
            "art_id": 3941566116,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "04 Dec 2015 03:45:56 GMT",
            "about": "Three soft drone-dub suites that are appropriate for Autumn. Recorded in three different sessions across two years, with principal location recording happening when I was away from home. A Blue Fume is melancholic night music, gentle techno for your ears and subconscious to ruminate on when you need the comforting nostalgia of home. Picking up sonically where Rurals left off, these three pieces are like a warm blanket of analog fuzz, tube-treated percussion, buoyant bass and tape-hiss bathed synthesizers.\nA second post-album session of more angular \"dance\" versions exists and will likely see a release in the coming months...",
            "credits": "released December 4, 2015\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded at (and away from) Botany Bay, 2013-2015. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number ABX48. Photography by Brian, Florida 2014.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a3941566116_0",
