            "item_id": 1128365890,
            "art_id": 3520141169,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "20 Jul 2011 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "A split-album between Monoaxial (aka Quantec/Sven Schienhammer) and Coppice Halifax (aka Milieu/Brian Grainger). A deep 72 minute trip, featuring three original tracks by each artist and a remix from each artist. Filled to the brim with low-end grooves, sheets of soft white noise and warm analog chords. Available in a limited edition of 100 copies on CD-R, packaged in slate grey paper sleeves with hand-stamped brown cardstock inserts.",
            "credits": "released July 20, 2011\nThis is Milieu Music number ABX10. Tracks 1/3/5 W/P by Sven. Tracks 2/4/6 W/P by Brian. Track 7 written by Brian, remixed by Sven. Track 8 written by Sven, remixed by Brian. Mastered by The Analog Botanist.\nwww.myspace.com/quantec\nwww.milieu-music.com",
