            "item_id": 3267396593,
            "art_id": 2309078007,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "07 Oct 2015 05:01:57 GMT",
            "about": "The second peripheral release of works connected to the upcoming Urceolatmospherion album is, itself, another album. While Nepenthesol is a more modest exercise in live psychedelic analog dance music, Ambusilicate is the inversion of this. Deep, tape-loop driven pieces of monolithic stature that pulse with the residual low end from a dance party a few blocks away. Ambient techno that is truly ambient by way of peeling away from the subject matter and viewing it aerially. Only from far distances are certain details observable.",
            "credits": "released October 7, 2015\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded at Botany Bay, September 2015, with hand-cut tape loops, analog hardware and extensive analog/digital realtime FX processing. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number MML103. Cover photography by Rudolf Kremers, used with permission.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a2309078007_0",
