            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "08 Nov 2016 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "Aubreeze is a four-track album of sunny, house-flavored oversaturated electronics. It could almost be considered part of a pair with Aerate, where that release is all bubbles and spacious humidity, Aubreeze is a measured walk through a park as the leaves fall. Taking (perhaps obvious) influences from Mille Plateaux, Shinichi Atobe, Dettinger and Luke Abbott, among others, Aubreeze presents four lengthy psychedelic pieces that ebb slowly across the horizon line, subtly splashing bits of color around as they go. Also, like Aerate, Aubreeze was partially recorded at Botany Bay in South Carolina (Pomwater) and completed after the move into the new studio in Ohio. The title track is in fact the first piece of music written and recorded from the ground up in the new studio.",
            "credits": "released November 8, 2016\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded at Botany Bay (#3) and WPW (#1/2/4), Summer-Autumn 2016. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number ABX59. Photograph taken by Brian in Columbia, SC, Summer 2016.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
