                "Cleveland"
            ],
            "item_id": 3084574000,
            "art_id": 318147461,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "25 Dec 2016 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "The second volume of Autochromata, deep techno experiments with a particular focus on exploring the textural and tonal possibilities of low bitrates, alternative sampling rates and other deliberately lossy setups. This volume contains three pieces, like the first volume, that are anchored by hypnotic rhythms and sustained bass notes that intertwine with the waves of processed chords and drones. The first two tracks are notably more energetic and developed than the previous De-Sat tracks, with the opener sounding remarkably close to something from Static Physics, while the third returns to that monochromatic minimalism again. Between the two is a watery dub that connects both ends of the album's spectrum.",
            "credits": "released December 25, 2016\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded at Botany Bay & White Pillar Workshop, 2013-2016. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Photography by Rudolf Kremers, lightly processed by Brian. Used with gracious permission. This is Milieu Music number ABX61.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a0318147461_0",
            "trackinfo": [
