            "datePublished": "12 Nov 2012 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "Blue Shape is an EP collecting three deep techno remix works constructed for Zander One's Iceberg, from his Echoate album. One-hundred percent of the sounds used to create these pieces came from Zander One's original track. These remixes were principally created live with various pieces of hardware, FX devices and computer, and laid to warm cassette tape. Cascading chord stabs and thin membranes of white noise succulently coat a field of round rhythmic forms. Globules of kick drum and sub bass coalesce with one another and counterpoint percussion is formed from the vaporous air itself.\nListen/download/buy Echoate by Zander One here:\nrecycledplastics.bandcamp.com/album/echoate/",
            "credits": "released November 12, 2012\nWritten by Zander One, produced and remixed by Coppice Halifax. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Recorded at Botany Bay, September 2012. This is Milieu Music number ABX16.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a2743265078_0",
