            "item_id": 2062460244,
            "art_id": 2552230442,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "13 Aug 2014 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "Dream-state fog rolls over dew covered kick drums left to fill up with rain water in the bottom of a ravine. Everything is blurry, slow like syrup, but if you squint and close one eye you can make out movements and a few round shapes in the abyss. Bliss lights up your mind and skin like a new drug, you could feel like this forever and never go back. Endless endless endless. Goodnight.",
            "credits": "released August 13, 2014\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded live at Botany Bay, August 13th 2014. Laid to tape, mutated and mastered by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number ABX34.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a2552230442_0",
