            "item_id": 3907069663,
            "art_id": 85746704,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "17 Jan 2014 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "Following the first year of the expansive Static Pharming series, it felt appropriate to issue this collection of works that predated and certainly helped build the sound of Static Pharming and, before it, Verdant Acre. Eleven tracks from various sources and formats, assembled here along the common thread of their droning, organic approach to composition. The material certainly isn't beatless - rather, it is a statement of deep techno coalescing and thickening from beneath a curtain of gigantic sound space. These pieces helped truly define the modern sound of Coppice Halifax, and for that they work together in a significant way that may not have been apparent until now. Everything presented on Collected Drone Works is either out of print or incredibly hard to come by in the physical format realm, so hopefully this issue of the Arboreal Digest reissue series sates some of the appetites of CH collectors, as well as newcomers.",
            "credits": "released January 17, 2014\nW/P by Coppice Halifax. Recorded at 114RKD & Botany Bay, various dates/sessions 2008-2011. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number AD10, and the 10th issue in the ongoing Arboreal Digest series.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
