            "about": "A short reprisal (of sorts) of the track \"Compost\" from last month's drone odyssey Compost Springtime Shed. Turns out massive synth drones and Analog Botany do indeed go together where composting is concerned. Recorded almost entirely live, two thick slabs of Halifaxian growth, built from the sounds of the original piece, and bathed in textural grit and compression much like earlier CH releases such as 1983. Now THAT is some funky recycling! Limited to 50 copies.",
            "credits": "released June 15, 2011\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Rebuilt from source (\"Compost\") by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number ABX8.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
