            "item_id": 1369804601,
            "art_id": 1283014573,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "09 Mar 2016 03:07:23 GMT",
            "about": "A lengthy, convoluted process that began with a truncated set of thirty-three one-bar loops taken from recently unearthed four-track master tapes for 2009 drone album. These thirty-three bars were then looped and mutated via all manner of analog and digital FX, including (but not limited to) FFT, low-pass filtering, pitch shifting and noise gating. A single drum machine - a ring modulated Boss DR-550 - was introduced into the mix to provide both contrast and counterpoint. Three more very different alternative mixes were produced, each going a little bit further down a tangential path than the others. In the end, Cubic Surf somewhat resembles the dance-oriented processing on Photovoltaic Fragments, and this album could be considered a companion piece to that. Another deeply alien experience for headphone and hi-fi listening.",
            "credits": "released March 9, 2016\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded across a week of sessions at Botany Bay, Valentine's Day weekend, 2016. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Cover photograph and design by Brian, taken on Instax film at an unnamed park, Autumn 2015. This is Milieu Music number ABX49.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a1283014573_0",
