                "minimalism",
                "techno",
                "Cleveland"
            ],
            "item_id": 2376143110,
            "art_id": 1960429072,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "02 Apr 2021 03:11:38 GMT",
            "about": "Three tracks, sporadically manifesting from the ashes of another minimal techno session from years past (see: Growth Markers -  coppicehalifax.bandcamp.com/album/growth-markers-phase-six-rhythmic-processing-recontextualization  ), that in many ways provide a bridge to other peripheral projects (such as Bike or even Vhom) as well as opening a new path forward for CH to explore. Inspired heavily by the minimalist techno of Mika Vainio / Ø, early SND, the first Sistol album, Thomas Brinkmann, LP5-era AE, Torsten Profrock and modern-era Omit recordings, CVX3 represents the typically glacial metabolic development of a longform CH album, redressed in sounds and events that are much more micro than macro, pointillist and welcoming of spaces and pauses, while still completely embracing of gridded rhythmic dynamism. CVX3 expresses many of these things while also managing to resemble almost nothing from the mainstream CH catalog, save for Deep Earth recordings, which these may very well owe the entirety of their structural makeup to. Greyscale electronic isolationism for minds looking to be momentarily erased.",
            "credits": "released April 2, 2021\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Regenerated and engineered at White Pillar, March 2020, using ABX64 as source compost. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Text and design by ABM&D. Photograph taken by Distrans Telekomm, Antarctica 1956, reproduced with permission. This is Milieu Music number ABX118.  milieu-music.com analogbotany.com",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a1960429072_0",
            "trackinfo": [
                {
                    "title": "Centrevillage",
                    "duration": "21:51",
