        {
            "url": "https://coppicehalifax.bandcamp.com/album/dusk-lion",
            "title": "Dusk Lion",
            "artist": "Coppice Halifax",
            "label": "Milieu Music Digital",
            "band_id": 2324625353,
            "classification": "paid",
            "tags": [
                "Electronic",
                "ambient",
                "ambient electronic",
                "ambient techno",
                "braindance",
                "deep",
                "deep techno",
                "drone",
                "drone techno",
                "dub",
                "dub techno",
                "idm",
                "minimal",
                "minimal techno",
                "techno",
                "Cleveland"
            ],
            "item_id": 1758337361,
            "art_id": 2277671221,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "22 Jun 2019 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "DUSK LION is the shorthand title given to a CH remix of the NIGHT ANTHELION recording, originally issued under my birthname. This mix was drafted during the remastering sessions for WHITE/NIGHT/BLACK/RED ANTHELION's collective 3xCD-R reissue as a way to revisit and explore the original audio tapes within an expanded and differently equipped studio setting. Until now, it has only been made available as part of that 3xCD-R reissue set, and after a few requests for it to be issued on its own, I've acquiesced and presented it here with its own catalog number and photographic artwork. Musically, DUSK LION would appeal to fans of things like ARBORIST'S EXCAVATIONS, CORNUCOPIAD, FISSURED BEACH and even VERDANT ACRE. Deep, electric drones covered in mossy textural drapes and evening hues, set against sub-bass rhythmic work and organic field recording spatter.\nEXPLORE THE ENTIRE ANTHELION SESSIONS FROM 2008 HERE:  briangrainger.bandcamp.com/album/anthelion-complete-2008-sessions",
            "credits": "released June 22, 2019\nWritten by Brian Grainger / Remixed and produced by Coppice Halifax. Recorded at the White Pillar Workshop, Spring 2019. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Photography and text by ABM&D. This is Milieu Music number AD40B.\nSpecial thanks to all of the members of the Milieu Music Fan Club at Patreon  (www.patreon.com/analogbotany).  With their continued support, more music like this release can happen! At the present moment, the members of the Fan Club are: Burt T / Brian S / Jake P / Christ S / Damian H / Levi G / Brian C / Arthur W / Joel B / Peter H-B / Rik J / Jose S / David P / Helge J / Peter C / Alan A / Alex G / Seth B / David T / Devin H / Mathieu L / Andy B / Francois H / Benoit P / J.C. Bastos\nMany humble thanks to the subscribers of the Deep Earth series. Without them, this music might not exist, and if it did, you might not be able to hear it. Support deep electronic mining initiatives today:  malfokusita.bandcamp.com",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a2277671221_0",
            "trackinfo": [
                {
                    "title": "Dusk Lion",
                    "duration": "37:45",
                    "lyrics": null,
                    "label": "Milieu Music Digital",
                    "track_id": 85386647,
                    "track_num": "1",
