                "Cleveland"
            ],
            "item_id": 539450061,
            "art_id": 3498683584,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "01 Apr 2022 05:45:50 GMT",
            "about": "DUSK RELICT is a double-album of two deep techno meditations, undertaken during a snow-flurried final gasp of Winter. Mining from the source sounds harvested during last year's DUSK VERSIONS remastered reissue, a distinctly Halifaxian palette is used to weave one last warm blanket in the dimming of the coldest season, a long sleep of resignation, willing and resolute in the need to be put to rest so that newer and greener things may come to fruition. It's been a difficult Winter, between the continued pandemic, the war in Europe and of course the tumultuous transitions in my personal life, and for this reason it felt not just apt, but essential, to mark the passage of the season with two definitive lines of demarcation - a view to the past, and a view to whatever comes next.",
            "credits": "released April 1, 2022\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded at White Pillar, March 2022, using source material from Dusk (AB12) in conjunction with the R-EW Audioholistics modular system and Korg Volca/ES-1 sampler units. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Design by ABM&D using a painting by Caspar David Friedrich, c. 1830s. This is Milieu Music number ABX125. (C) + (P) Oscillog ASCAP 2022. All nights preserved.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a3498683584_0",
            "trackinfo": [
                {
                    "title": "Dusk Relict",
                    "duration": "39:51",
