            "item_id": 3829828217,
            "art_id": 1659181546,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "04 Dec 2020 06:02:41 GMT",
            "about": "DUSTY ACRE offers up two Halifaxian reconstitutions of source material from Milieu's A DUSTY BOX OF OLD MEMORIES album, arranged during the remastering process in July of 2015. These pieces, not entirely distant or dissimilar to things like VERDANT ACRE or URCEOLATMOSPHERION, recall the tape-bleached Casio palette used on the original Milieu recordings, juxtaposed against a mutant-parametric drum kit and bassline, generated using various loopers and low-bit samplers at the time. Overgrown and wildly tangential, these sessions will appeal to fans of albums like A BLUE FUME, CORNUCOPIAD or ELUVIAN II.\nNOTE: For listeners looking to hear the entire remastered A DUSTY BOX OF OLD MEMORIES album, these two mixes are appended as a second disc in the limited edition 2xCD-R set, available at the Milieu page:  milieumusic.bandcamp.com/album/a-dusty-box-of-old-memories-expanded-remastered",
            "credits": "released December 4, 2020\nWritten by Milieu. Remixed and produced by Coppice Halifax, July 2015, at Botany Bay, SC. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Photograph by A.C. with post-processing by Brian. This is Milieu Music number AD18B.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a1659181546_0",
