            "item_id": 902945788,
            "art_id": 2498107301,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "08 May 2020 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "...EARTH 52 in YEAR FIVE of the DEEP EARTH series...\nLa tondado de tuŝo, eksplodanta en ĉiuj direktoj sen zorgo aŭ konsekvenco. Fragmentoj de tio, kio estis difinitaj sekcioj de la memo, eksplodis en ŝtormon de statika kaj bruo. Ĉiu peco, ĉiu ero, malgranda universo plena de novaj steloj, novaj sunoj, blindigantaj kaj vivaj. Bruligitaj tra tavolo post tavolo, paralelaj realaĵoj kuniĝis en cindron.",
            "credits": "released May 8, 2020\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded at White Pillar across two nights of April 2020, using an IK Multimedia Uno Drum, a Boss DR-660, Mutable Inst. Clouds, a Grass Click-Tone Control Module sequenced by a Behringer MS-1, and an effects array including a Digitech WH-4, Synthrotek PT2399, BBE Two Timer, Danelectro Reel Echo, Ibanez Phase Modulator, with control voltage automation via a Korg MS-20, three Moogerfoogers and the routing matrix on an Arturia Microbrute. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Photography and design by ABM&D. This is Milieu Music number EARTH 52, and 52nd in the Deep Earth catalog.  www.milieu-music.com  /  www.analogbotany.com\nSpecial thanks to all of the members of the Milieu Music Fan Club at Patreon  (www.patreon.com/analogbotany).  With their continued support, more music like this release can happen! At the present moment, the members of the Fan Club are: Burt T / Brian S / Jake P / Chris S / Damian H / Peter H-B / Rik J / Jose S / Michael R / Joel B / JC Bastos / David P / Helge J / Peter C / Alan A / Alex G / Seth B / David T / Devin H / Mathieu L / Andy B / Francois H / Benoit P / Juan D / Gavin C / Tarek E / Friedrich W / Jonathan W / Andrew O'K / Peter T / Daniel F / Gordon C / Alex K / Gavin M / Balz B / Miles B / Tony S / Sean W / Alex B / Justin W / David HS / K. F. / Steven A / Giovanni R / Tyler L / James S / Joe S\nMany humble thanks to the subscribers of the Deep Earth series. Without them, this music might not exist, and if it did, you might not be able to hear it. Support deep electronic mining initiatives today:  malfokusita.bandcamp.com",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a2498107301_0",
