            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "06 Apr 2015 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "Three mostly live performances of the Static Pharming: Year Two piece Eluvian, which was originally constructed completely from field recordings of my backyard, local trains passing by, rocks in mud and fireworks. Eluvian II takes the original tape loops of the trains and the backyard and composts them into a gigantic ever-shifting wall of organic sound sculpture, a pulsing backdrop for drum machines, textured percussion and treated rhythm and bass elements to provide a heavy romp through a crackling forest. Similar in sound palette and approach to things like Cornucopiad and Static Physics, to be played loud!",
            "credits": "released April 6, 2015\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded live at Foxhill, with post-production processing and minimal overdubbing conducted at Botany Bay, Spring 2015. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. This is Milieu Music number ABX40.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a3184849051_0",
