            "credits": "released October 2, 2020\nW/P by Brian Grainger. Recorded late Summer 2020 at White Pillar, using source material from the 2019-2020 Anthelion/Compost sessions and Post Process, in conjunction with Korg ES-1/KP-2/Volca Sample, Akai S2800, Boss RC-20 and the R-EW Audioholistics modular processing path. Mastered by The Analog Botanist. Text and photography by Brian / No filters Summer 2020. This is Milieu Music number ABX115D.  milieu-music.com analogbotany.com\nSpecial thanks to all of the members of the Milieu Music Fan Club at Patreon (  patreon.com/analogbotany  ). With their continued support, more music like this release can happen! At the present moment, the members of the Fan Club are: Burt T / Brian S / Jake P / Chris S / Tyler L / David HS / Peter H-B / Rik J / Jose AMS / Tarek E / Kevan F / Justin W / Michael R / JC Bastos / Helge J / Peter C / Alan A / Seth B / Daniel F / Joel B / Charlie 82 / Devin H / Mathieu L / Andy B / Francois H / Benoit P / Alex G / Rimas C / James S / Joseph S / Giovanni R / Gavin McF / Balz B / Juan D / Gavin C / David P / Andrew O'K / Peter T / Jona W / Alex B / Axl559 / Gordon C / Frank S V / Aba D O / Bernd H / Miles B / Tony S / Sean W\nMany humble thanks to the subscribers of the Deep Earth series and the Vibratelepathic Antiviral Broadcasts. Without them, this music might not exist, and if it did, you might not be able to hear it. Support deep electronic mining initiatives today:  malfokusita.bandcamp.com vibratelepathos.bandcamp.com",
